title: For Sale/Trade:  RARE Manurin PP
postcontent:
This is a very rare find. This is a licensed copy of the Walther PP. After WW2 Germany could not manufacturer any firearms, and the French company Manurhin picked up the reigns and started manufacturing this weapon many have copied. CZ & Sig both have firearms based off of this model and the Russian Markarov is also based off of this. The serial number puts this one being one of the first off the line in 1952. They actually produced the PP until the mid 80's, and even if the firearm may say Walther, it was still actually produced by Manhurin. This is one of the few to have the actual markings from the French factory.
Comes with a case, two holsters, and two magazines. I've fired hundreds through it as im sure hundreds have gone in before without any problems.
